                                         JOHANNESBURG - A matric pupil has died in KwaZulu-Natal after being hit by a car just moments after writing her final exam. Two other pupils were seriously injured when the driver of the car lost control and crashed into the group opposite Southway Mall on Monday. Emergency services say the three were walking home on the pavement after their last day of high school. Rescue Care's Ceron Lennox said: “There was a witness who said he was all over the road, hit the pavement and landed a few metres away from the accident scene. but the actual cause of the accident is unknown. Law officials are on scene and they have already started investigations.”